},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["","n19357","n19358","n19359"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8E%D8%AF%D9%8E%D9%84%D9%8E"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to dangle, to hang, to suspend","tags":["transitive"],"examples":[{"text":"[..] عَنِ ٱبْنِ عُمَرَ، قَالَ كَانَ النَّبِيُّ صَلَّى اللهُ عَلَيْهِ وَسَلَّمَ إِذَا ٱعْتَمَّ سَدَلَ عِمَامَتَهُ بَيْنَ كَتِفَيْهِ. قَالَ نَافِعٌ وَكَانَ ٱبْنُ عُمَرَ يَسْدِلُ عِمَامَتَهُ بَيْنَ كَتِفَيْهِ. قَالَ عُبَيْدُ اللهِ وَرَأَيْتُ القَاسِمَ وَسَالِمًا يَفْعَلَانِ ذَلِكَ [..]\n[..] ʕani bni ʕumara, qāla kāna n-nabiyyu ṣallā llāhu ʕalayhi wasallama ʔiḏā ʕtamma sadala ʕimāmatahu bayna katifayhi. qāla nāfiʕun wakāna bnu ʕumara yasdilu ʕimāmatahu bayna katifayhi. qāla ʕubaydu llāhi waraʔaytu l-qāsima wasāliman yafʕalāni ḏalika [..]","english":"[..] from Ibn 'Umar, he said, \"When wearing a headcloth, the Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, would hang it between his shoulders.\" Nafi' said, \"Ibn 'Umar would [likewise] hang his headcloth between his shoulders.\" 'Ubaidullah said, \"And I saw Al-Qasim and Salim do that [also].\" [..]"}]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/sa.da.la/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n19357","headword_ar":"سُدْلٌ","root":"sdl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sidolN","text_ar":"سِدْلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[the former written in a copy of the M"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sadol","text_ar":"سَدْل"},{"kind":"text","text":", but said in the K to be with damm,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A veil,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"curtain:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl. [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suduwlN","text_ar":"سُدُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asodaAlN","text_ar":"اَسْدَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asodulN","text_ar":"اَسْدُلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) In a verse of Homeyd Ibn-Thowr, as it is related by Yaakoob,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~uduwl","text_ar":"السُّدُول"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used as a sing., because it is of a measure which is [in some instances] that of a sing., such as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~uduws","text_ar":"السُّدُوس"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning a sort of garment: but others relate it differently, saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~adiyl","text_ar":"السَّدِيل"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is correctly a sing. (M.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sidonN","text_ar":"سِدْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["M","K"]},{"entry_id":"n19358","headword_ar":"سِدْلٌ","root":"sdl","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A string of gems"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"jewels:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a string of pearls"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"large pearls, reaching to the breast:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suduwlN","text_ar":"سُدُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) ―         -b2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sudolN","text_ar":"سُدْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["S","M","K"]},{"entry_id":"n19359","headword_ar":"سَدَلٌ","root":"sdl","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An inclining."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.) [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asodalu","text_ar":"اَسْدَلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":[]}]}}